olive oil
1 eggplant
40 g plant-based butter
1 packet basmati rice
1 bag baby broccoli
1 bag cavolo nero kale
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 packet tahini
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
3 clove garlic
1.5 cup water (for the rice)
¾ cup water (for the sauce)

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the eggplant into small chunks, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season to taste and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the eggplant is roasting, finely chop the garlic. In a medium saucepan, melt 1/2 the plant-based butter with a dash of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook 1/2 the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the basmati rice, water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt, stir, then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to low and cover with a lid. Cook for 10 minutes, then remove from the heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

Trim and halve the baby broccoli. Roughly chop the cavolo nero kale. In a small bowl, combine the garlic dip and tahini. Set aside. Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Toast the flaked almonds until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

When the rice has 10 minutes cook time remaining, return the frying pan to a medium-high heat a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the baby broccoli until tender, 4-5 minutes. Add the kale and remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the tomato paste and chermoula spice blend and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the water (for the sauce) and remaining butter and cook until slightly reduced, 1-3 minutes. Remove from the heat, then add the eggplant to the sauce. Stir to coat.

Divide the garlic rice between bowls. Top with the Middle Eastern eggplant and baby broccoli. Drizzle over the tahini garlic dip. Garnish with the toasted almonds to serve.